{"id": "1446787277476073546", "channel_id": "1326453691527594035", "author_id": "896400240192675850", "author_name": "hskzu", "content": "draft priority 101:\n1. Check relic effect before thinking about other, some effect just straight up destroy your plan (chime discard every turn is not friendly with prepare type of card)\n2. Make sure your priority is correct in picking wheel/awakener first\n3. Don't pick awakener in the same color if your opponent already pick it, that's a freebie choice for last stretch the other 2 left unpicked is free for you\n4. See your opponent pick, if they pick someone like caecus/alva for example, you can screw them over by picking the strike wheels and left them with none", "timestamp": "2025-12-06T08:56:06.958000+00:00"}
{"id": "1446839114983800902", "channel_id": "1326453691527594035", "author_id": "226944773410258946", "author_name": "mengluo", "content": "-Look at the relic first. This one for example makes Tawil unpickable because copying Tawil's cards is op.\n-Figure out the win condition. This game looks like it will go long since the pool is low damage and a lot of healing/shield. Scaling awakeners are the win condition here.\n-Figure out what counters the win condition. Doll is very good here for dispelling debuffs. Sea Festival is good for delaying your opponent's win condition by a turn.\nI would prioritize Doll then Sea Festival then generic good wheels here.\n-Finally, complain about rng because you bottom deck every good card again while your opponent opens the nuts.", "timestamp": "2025-12-06T12:22:05.983000+00:00", "type": 19, "mentions": ["459852677262606336"], "attachments": [{"id": "1446839114740662295", "filename": "Screenshot_1935_-_Copy.png", "content_type": "image/png", "size": 1443924, "url": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1326453691527594035/1446839114740662295/Screenshot_1935_-_Copy.png?ex=6a35346d&is=6a33e2ed&hm=faf5b8a24a7d1570c4c5182c1589f7b24dd8bc8c1206aac74d56f9e2e82aeed1&"}], "reply_to": "1446758104040734830"}
{"id": "1446841849795973291", "channel_id": "1326453691527594035", "author_id": "108392615644278784", "author_name": "alistiel", "content": "Personally, I think in this position you always take roulette wheel. It's one of the only wheels you can play across your entire team, so if it's in your hand when Jenkin's ult is up, you can reliably get it on multiple characters.", "timestamp": "2025-12-06T12:32:58.013000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": "2025-12-06T12:35:35.669000+00:00"}
{"id": "1446842821838373025", "channel_id": "1326453691527594035", "author_id": "108392615644278784", "author_name": "alistiel", "content": "Murphy's great too because Murphy has really high value on her ultimate this way, but you have to get a Reality Imitation with her, and they can now get +2 arithmetica or +50 aliemus, aNd It'S rAnDoM", "timestamp": "2025-12-06T12:36:49.766000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": "2025-12-06T12:37:21.224000+00:00"}
